body.p: BUNGALOW SCHOOL Mrs. Mary E. Day has returned from White Lake where she visited for several weeks At the home of her daughter, Mrs. Peter Metelski. Mr. and Mrs. Joe Stoltz and daugh- ter of Ringle called at the Gust Hanke home Thursday. Mr. and Mrs. Julius Nevinskl and children were Wednesday evening vis- itors at tho L. H. Brehmer home. Ray Fenske has returned from a visit at Waupun. Mr. and Mrs. Lester Kasson and children of ClintonviUe spent the week- end at the Gust Hanke home. On Sun- day Mr. and Mrs. Kasson and Mr. and Mrs. Marlyn Hanke visited at Antigo. Mr. and Mrs. Ed. Ullenbrauck of Ringle also called at the Hanke home on Sunday. Mr. and Mrs. Julius Nevinski called at the Max Ssews home Saturday eve- ning. Neighbors gathered at the Fred Fenske home Sunday evening. Cards were played, after which lunch was served. Last Saturday evening {he gathering was held at the Gust Hanke home. Arthur Petersen, Alfred Hegewaid, Ray Vanderkooy, Elroy Peterson and Billie Burnett visited at the Harry Vanderkooy and Vernon Petersen homes at Menasha Sunday. Rupert, Ernest and Lorraine Stews. Ethel and Leonard Brehmer and Joyce Jacobsen attended a program at the Elderon State Graded School Monday evening.
